Carapace fairly large, elongate in lateral outline, inequilateral (
Fig. 1A, B
), with fairly ramified radial pore canals (
Fig. 1C, D
). Greatest height at midlength, slightly posterior to muscle scars. Length approximately 2.5 times maximum height. Lateral surface with three or four small subcircular, white, opaque patches; other irregular patches in variable positions, but mainly near margins. Dark brown cuticle around central opaque patch, and at anterodorsal and posterior regions of valve surface. Dorsal margin evenly low-arched, with indistinct dorsal angle. Posterodorsal margin fairly straight. Anterior margin (
Fig. 1C
) unevenly rounded. Ventral margin rounded anteriorly; with shallow indentation, and only slightly upswung posteriorly. Posterior angle rounded (
Fig. 1D
), dorsal and ventral margins forming an angle of about 50°. Zone of concrescence (
Fig. 1C, D
) of moderate width, irregular. Adductor muscle scar pattern

